  + [purpose] is identify whether any blocker remains before an eventual explicit RH-only first-bookend staging direction
  + [not_purpose] is staging, committing, branch creation, broad .sop mutation, runtime code change, test execution, deterministic math execution, proof claim, disproof claim, zero certification, or route expansion
  + [proof_status] is readiness_review_not_rh_evidence

& [ReadinessContract] is bounded
  + [package_input] is FirstBookendPackageManifest001
  + [test_baseline_input] is WorktreeIntegrityReview001 with 36 passing tests
  + [commit_scope_input] is CommitScopeReview001 with RH-only default and CurrentFocalPoint optional
  + [required_checks] are package coherence, stable runtime/tool/test surface, ignored-runtime exclusion, contradiction blockers, and user-gated staging boundary
  + [required_result] is blocker_found, no_blocker_found, or user_direction_required

& [ConstraintContract] is bounded
  + [allowed_output] is readiness classification and next action recommendation
  + [blocked_output] is staging command, commit command, test run, branch action, proof interpretation, new computation, or package broadening
  + [route_if_no_blocker] is report that the remaining transition is explicit user staging/commit direction rather than another self-generated package record

& [FirstBookendReadinessCheckpointSJS] is the specification justification trace
  + [processed_stage_set] is source_preserved, delineated, canonicalized, constraint_checked, justified, and readiness_scoped
  + [processing_result] is accepted_readiness_checkpoint_contract
  + [reasoning_result] is readiness review can close the non-staging governance chain by naming whether the package is blocked or merely user-gated

(first_bookend_readiness_checkpoint) :readiness checkpoint: /blocker check before user-gated staging/ |staging, commit, test run, proof claims|
  + [inside] is package coherence, stable tool/test posture, ignored-runtime exclusion, blocker classification, and next action recommendation
  + [boundary] is no staging, no commit, no test run, no broad .sop mutation, no math execution, no proof claim
  |outside| theorem authority, zero certification, runtime implementation, branch change, and platform-wide authority inclusion
